{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "We use the HH-RLHF datasetfoot_9 as the training dataset, which consists of human preference data (about helpfulness and harmlessness) [2] and Red teaming data [99].",
    "During training, we set the client number as 5, where we randomly sample 2 clients to be available for each round.",
    "These clients hold 161k data samples in total.",
    "During the evaluation, we consider two aspects, namely harmlessness and helpfulness, to avoid overly pursuing harmlessness at the huge cost of helpfulness.",
    "For harmlessness, we consider the harmlessness score from HHH [100] and the rejection rate on harmful questions from AdvBench [101]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We use the HH-RLHF datasetfoot_9 as the training dataset, which consists of human preference data (about helpfulness and harmlessness) [2] and Red teaming data [99].",
    "For harmlessness, we consider the harmlessness score from HHH [100] and the rejection rate on harmful questions from AdvBench [101]."
